                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_kʼūx" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼūx</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼox</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>рука</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>arm</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кисть руки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>hand</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>палец</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>finger</q></tr></sense></sense><re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼaxkʼūx</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>палец ноги</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>toe</q></tr></sense></re><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼūxdaræn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼoxdaræn</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кольцо</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>ring</q></tr></sense></re></re><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼūxmærzæn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼoxmærzæn</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>полотенце</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>towel</q></tr></sense></re><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼūxoj</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼoxoj</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>безрукий</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>armless</q></tr></sense></re><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼūxylxæcæg</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼoxbælxwæcæg</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>шафер</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bridesman</q></tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>sarǧi kʼox</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>лука седла</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>fork (about a saddle)</q></tr></sense><note>(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 94</biblScope></bibl>)</note></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>ḱʼīzī dærzæg kʼūxæj cæstysyg asqawdta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>грязной шершавой рукой он смахнул слезу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he brushed away a tear with his dirty rough hand</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>69</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cwanon sykʼījy līʒgæ k˳y fedta, wæd jæ kʼūxtæ kæræʒījyl nyxxosta æmæ nyddīs kodta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>когда охотник увидел серну бегущей, он хлопнул руку об руку и поразился</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>when the hunter saw the chamois running, he clapped his hands once and marveled</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 39</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ḱynʒ yn radta avd fæltæry jæ daræs kʼaxæj kʼūxmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>невестка дала ему семь смен одежды с ноги до руки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the daughter-in-law gave him seven shifts of clothes from foot to arm</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>cuppærkʼoxūg æfsæjnag sagænttæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>четырехпалые железные вилы</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>four-fingered iron pitchfork</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>245%l2%l</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>ḱʼīzī dærzæg kʼūxæj cæstysyg asqawdta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>грязной шершавой рукой он смахнул слезу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he brushed away a tear with his dirty rough hand</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>69</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cwanon sykʼījy līʒgæ k˳y fedta, wæd jæ kʼūxtæ kæræʒījyl nyxxosta æmæ nyddīs kodta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>когда охотник увидел серну бегущей, он хлопнул руку об руку и поразился</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>when the hunter saw the chamois running, he clapped his hands once and marveled</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 39</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ḱynʒ yn radta avd fæltæry jæ daræs kʼaxæj kʼūxmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>невестка дала ему семь смен одежды с ноги до руки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the daughter-in-law gave him seven shifts of clothes from foot to arm</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>cuppærkʼoxūg æfsæjnag sagænttæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>четырехпалые железные вилы</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>four-fingered iron pitchfork</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>245%l2%l</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Как и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼax"/> ‘нога’, идет из кавказского субстрата; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>kujg</w> <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>. Есть ли какая-то древняя связь с <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/> <w>kek</w> <gloss><q>ручка</q></gloss></mentioned> — трудно сказать. Исконно иранским словом для ‘руки’ было <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/>, которое и сейчас употребительно, в особенности в устойчивых сочетаниях и в сложных словах. — Ср. другие названия руки — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/>, а также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fad"/> ‘нога’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>78, 105, 117</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It comes from Caucasian substrate, as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼax"/> ‘foot’ does; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>kujg</w> <gloss><q>arm</q></gloss></mentioned>. It is difficult to say whether there is any ancient relation to <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/> <w>kek</w> <gloss><q>small hand</q></gloss></mentioned>. The original Iranian word for ‘hand’ was <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/>, which is still widely used, especially in collocations and compound words. — Cf. other names for a hand — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/>, and also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fad"/> ‘foot’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>78, 105, 117</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>